1. Systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE): This autoimmune disease can affect multiple organs, including the lungs, kidneys, joints, and skin. Pleural effusion, proteinuria, synovitis, and nasal ulcers are all potential symptoms of SLE.

2. Rheumatoid arthritis (RA): This autoimmune disease primarily affects the joints, but it can also cause other symptoms, such as pleural effusion and proteinuria. Nasal ulcers are less common in RA, but they can occur.

3. Scleroderma: This autoimmune disease can cause thickening and scarring of the skin, as well as damage to internal organs, including the lungs, kidneys, and joints. Pleural effusion, proteinuria, synovitis, and nasal ulcers are all potential symptoms of scleroderma.

4. Granulomatosis with polyangiitis (GPA): This vasculitis affects small and medium-sized blood vessels, and it can cause damage to the lungs, kidneys, and joints. Pleural effusion, proteinuria, synovitis, and nasal ulcers are all potential symptoms of GPA.

5. Microscopic polyangiitis (MPA): This vasculitis affects small blood vessels, and it can cause damage to the lungs, kidneys, and joints. Pleural effusion, proteinuria, synovitis, and nasal ulcers are all potential symptoms of MPA.

6. Eosinophilic granulomatosis with polyangiitis (EGPA): This vasculitis affects small and medium-sized blood vessels, and it can cause damage to the lungs, kidneys, and joints. Pleural effusion, proteinuria, synovitis, and nasal ulcers are all potential symptoms of EGPA.

7. Mixed connective tissue disease (MCTD): This autoimmune disease shares features of several other autoimmune diseases, including SLE, RA, and scleroderma. Pleural effusion, proteinuria, synovitis, and nasal ulcers are all potential symptoms of MCTD.

8. Sjögrens syndrome: This autoimmune disease primarily affects the salivary and lacrimal glands, but it can also cause other symptoms, such as pleural effusion, proteinuria, and synovitis. Nasal ulcers are less common in Sjögrens syndrome, but they can occur.

9. Behçets disease: This inflammatory disease affects blood vessels and can cause a variety of symptoms, including skin lesions, oral ulcers, genital ulcers, eye inflammation, and joint pain. Pleural effusion, proteinuria, synovitis, and nasal ulcers are less common in Behçets disease, but they can occur.

10. Sarcoidosis: This inflammatory disease can affect multiple organs, including the lungs, lymph nodes, skin, and eyes. Pleural effusion, proteinuria, synovitis, and nasal ulcers are all potential symptoms of sarcoidosis.
